Given - I am logged in
And I go to Page 3 
And select 'Yes' in 'Contrast enhanced' 
And I go to Page 7 Cranial MRT
And I select 'Finding' radio button 

When I select 'Pathology' from the dropdown 
And I select 'Characterization II' tab 

Then 'Parenchymal defect' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Cysts' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Capsule' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Signal voids' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Fluid-fluid level' checkbox is enabled 

And 'Confluent' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Mass-effect' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Infiltration' checkbox is enabled 

And 'Perifocal edema' checkbox is enabled 
And 'Abscess' checkbox is enabled 

And 'Midline shift' checkbox is enabled 

And 'Involvement of ventricles' checkbox is enabled 

And 'No' radio button is enabled 
And 'Low' radio button is enabled 
And 'Strong' radio button is enabled 

When I select 'Parenchymal defect' checkbox 
Then checkbox is checked
When I select 'Hemorrhage' checkbox 
Then checkbox is checked
When I select 'Necrosis' checkbox
Then checkbox is checked
When I select 'Calcification' checkbox 
Then checkbox is checked
